BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:New Moon Hike\, Brown County State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260516T210000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260516T230000
UID:cffdf85af9d1e56f52dc18fe5f5a6707@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Full Moons occur when the Moon is fully illuminated by the Sun
 \, allowing viewers on Earth to see the full circle. It&#39\;s typically t
 he brightest night of the month. The New Moon is the darkest night of the 
 month\, when dark side of the Moon faces Earth. We&#39\;re going on a hike
  on the darkest night of the month! We will meet at the Park Office/Fire T
 ower Parking lot at 9pm to hike Trail 10. Please note Trail 10 should be c
 onsidered very rugged in the dark and involves hiking from one of the high
 est elevations in the park to one of the lowest. The route is 2.2 miles an
 d will take about two hours. Red flashlights help us preserve night vision
 . We have some to lend out\, but it is wise to bring your own if you have 
 one. Brown County State Park Naturalists&#39\; hike cancellation policy: H
 ikes will be cancelled for safety reasons. Rain by itself is not enough to
  cancel a hike. Cancellation reasons: Heat index above 105 degrees F Cold 
 below 0 degrees F A strong wind advisory (for trails in the woods)
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Park office\, 1405 S.R. 46 W\, Nashvill
 e\, IN 
URL:on.in.gov/BrownCountySP
X-SOURCE:Brown County State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Full Moon Hike\, Brown County State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260530T210000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260530T220000
UID:236ea49f77e767cec55a86818a268f83@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Join a park naturalist for a guided night hike on the Salt Cre
 ek Trail! The Full Moon is the brightest night of the month\, leading to i
 nteresting views along the creek. Learn about May&#39\;s second full moon 
 this year\, the Blue Moon. The Salt Creek Trail is rated very easy\, but s
 hould be considered moderate in the dark. The trail has some minor slopes\
 , a short stretch of lawn\, and possible wet or icy spots depending on wea
 ther. Our route is&nbsp\; about 2 miles total and will take about an hour 
 to complete. Please do not bring pets on night hikes. Red flashlights are 
 preferred for night vision and can be loaned to hikers on request.
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Olympic Pool parking lot\, 1405 S.R. 46
  W\, Nashville\, IN 
URL:https://on.in.gov/BrownCountySP
X-SOURCE:Brown County State Park
END:VEVENT
